---
title: Fresh, Homemade Carrot, Pancetta and Lentil Soup with Herb Foccacia (5 MEAL)
description: The weather is warming up but we thought there should be one last hurrah for this homemade bowl of love! In Italy when you come to the bottom of your bowl it’s common to “fare la scarpetta” which (randomly) means “do the shoe”. It’s the action of wiping your plate, though fortunately we’ve provided you with some fresh foccacia rather than an old shoe!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/554a6104f8b25e1e268b457a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/554a6104f8b25e1e268b457a.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/fresh-homemade-carrot-pancetta-and-lentil-soup-554a6104f8b25e1e268b457a
time required: 40 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 613 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  protein: 20 g
author: HelloFresh
---

Peel and dice about ⅔ of a cup of the @onion{3/4%onion}(peeled and diced), the @celery stick{1}(diced) and @carrot{1}(peeled and diced). Peel and chop the @potato{1.5%potato} into roughly 2cm chunks. Peel and finely dice the @garlic clove{1}(finely diced). Finely chop the @coriander{3}(finely chopped) and thoroughly rinse the @red split lentils{1/2%cup}.

Cook the @chilli flakes{1/2%tsp}, onion, garlic, celery and carrot in a @olive oil{1%tbsp} on medium heat in a #pot{} for around ~{6%minutes}, or until soft.

> If you're not too keen on spiciness, add less chilli flakes!

Add the potatoes and continue to cook for another ~{5%minutes}.

Add @water{600%ml} and bring the pan to a gentle simmer. Add in the @vegetable stock pot{1}, the @chopped tomatoes{1%tin}, veg and the rinsed lentils. Allow the mixture to simmer for ~{20%minutes} or until the lentils are soft.

In a separate pan, cook the @British smoked bacon lardons{1/3%cup} in a @olive oil{1%tsp} on medium heat. Cook the pancetta for around ~{5%minutes} or until it is crispy around the edges. Drain the pancetta of excess oil and keep to the side.

> Lay the pancetta on some kitchen paper to let it soak up the remaining oil.

Turn your #oven{} up to 100 degrees and put the @herb focaccia{1%focaccia} in for a few mins to warm it up.

Stir the coriander into the soup. Serve it with pancetta sprinkled across the top and big chunks of warm focaccia on the side.